The president does not want to avoid this topic because he is aware that he receives this award by being a president who is waging a war in two countries at the moment.
He reinforced the war effort even a few days ago by sending additional units to Afghanistan, which no one of his critics will forget to emphasize.
At the ceremony, Obama will also receive a gold medal, a diploma and a check worth ten million Swedish kronor (approximately €1.1 million).
He plans to donate it to charity, but he has not yet decided specifically which.
His busy program will then take him and his wife to a banquet including, in addition to the King and Queen of Norway, the head of government and 250 other guests.
Obama was quite reluctant to this price at first.
He mentioned, for example, having the feeling that he did not deserve it fully.
He has also repeated several times that this is not a prize for him alone, but for all those who defend the same values as him.
As soon as the announcement, he said it would be for him a “invitation to action.”
