After almost two years, the light commercial vehicle market is beginning to see some light at the end of the tunnel.
The 9,425 vehicles registered in November in Spain represent an increase of 12.6% compared to 2008 and, more importantly, they represent the first increase after 22 consecutive months of decline, according to figures from the patronage union of manufacturers Anfac and Ganvam, that of dealers.
