Building a garage in four stages
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex guarantees that the user gets a quote in just four steps: identify the vehicle, search for the spare part, create a quote and generate it.
The ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially to convince the older professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to the use of new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, including 666 tourist, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Naturally, to use it, a computer and an internet connection are required.
Once the model to be repaired is identified by its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and the necessary part is selected.
The user can include variables such as labour price, increases or discounts, and then print the quote to return it to the customer.
AudaTaller is not an estimate tool like AudaPlus, but a catalog of references.
The main difference between these two systems is that the one for garages does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which can be subject to credit.
Currently, Audatex is working to make these images three-dimensional.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with a very good eye, as it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it to see the inner side.
